50|$|Treatment for zoster ophthalmicus {{is similar}} to {{standard}} treatment for shingles at other sites. A recent trial comparing aciclovir with its prodrug, <b>valaciclovir,</b> demonstrated similar efficacies in treating this form of the disease. The significant advantage of <b>valaciclovir</b> over aciclovir is its dosing of only 3 times/day (compared with aciclovir's 5 times/day dosing), which could make it more convenient for people and improve adherence with therapy.|$|E
